---
/**
 * Proofkit Overlay - the on-page content-review annotation layer.
 *
 * Part of the isolated Proofkit package (src/plugins/proofkit/ - see ./README.md).
 * Toggle the whole tool on/off with PROOFKIT_ENABLED in ./config.ts.
 *
 * Closed-URL tool for the content team to review the LIVE site. In review mode
 * the page desaturates (B/W) but stays scrollable; existing comments show as
 * numbered pins anchored to their elements; clicking anywhere adds a new comment.
 * Comments can only be ADDED here - never edited or deleted (that's dashboard-side).
 *
 * DESIGN NOTES
 * - Ships as ONE bundled, deferred, cached module. Renders NOTHING and injects no
 *   styles until review mode is armed (perf-budget safe for real visitors).
 * - Arm: signing in at /review (Proofkit Login sets `reviewMode`; persists per tab,
 *   `?review=0` signs out). Never arms on the tool's own /review + /reviewdash routes.
 * - Anchoring: each comment stores page path, a CSS selector, a text snippet, and
 *   click coords; pins re-project onto the element's current rect each frame.
 * - Storage: talks to the Cloudflare Worker (WORKER_URL) when set, else a
 *   localStorage demo store so the flow is testable before deploy.
 *
 * THIN ADAPTER: all behaviour + injected styles live in the framework-neutral core
 * (./core/overlay.js). This file only bridges the build-time Worker URL to the core
 * and loads it; BaseLayout renders it site-wide, dormant until review mode is armed.
 */
import { WORKER_URL } from './config';
---

{/* Bridge the build-time Worker URL to the framework-neutral core (window global). */}
<script is:inline set:html={`window.PROOFKIT_WORKER_URL=${JSON.stringify(WORKER_URL)}`}></script>

{/* Bundled + deferred module - one shared cached file, dormant for real visitors. */}
<script>import './core/overlay.js';</script>
